d be changed as joint axes can normally take any value.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>In the current version of gazebo, the joint axes are visualized via a small circle mark in 3D at the top of the joint frame axes. Now this only allows to display joint axes which are aligned with one of the canonical axes of the joint frame. If the joint axis is not a frame's canonical axis, there is no display. This should be changed as joint axes can normally take any value.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": null, "state": "closed", "version": {"name": "all", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/versions/225575.json"}}}, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2014-10-01T11:37:05.460025+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2016-09-14T19:44:48.012276+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 1288}